<h2>What it is</h2>

<p>
  Tesselage is a desktop application that brings together live data from dozens of sources and displays them on an interactive 3D globe. Aircraft in flight, vessels at sea, satellites in orbit, weather patterns, seismic events, delivery trucks on route &mdash; all fused into a single, photorealistic view on your workstation. Think of what happens when Google Earth meets an intelligence-grade operations dashboard.
</p>

<hr />

<h2>Core capabilities</h2>

<div class="feature-block">
  <div class="feature-label">Fusion</div>
  <h4>Multi-source live data</h4>
  <p>
    Pulls real-time feeds from open sources &mdash; aviation trackers, maritime AIS, satellite orbital data, weather services, seismic sensors, traffic incident feeds, wildfire detection, and fleet telematics. Instead of opening six different websites, Tesselage consolidates everything into one unified, continuously updated view.
  </p>
</div>

<div class="feature-block">
  <div class="feature-label">Intelligence</div>
  <h4>Natural language queries</h4>
  <p>
    Ask the system questions in plain language: "Show me all vessels that went dark near the Red Sea in the last hour," "Which trucks are closest to the Austrian border right now?" A local AI model understands the current scene and answers in context &mdash; no cloud dependency, no data leaving your machine.
  </p>
</div>

<div class="feature-block">
  <div class="feature-label">Visualization</div>
  <h4>Photorealistic 3D globe</h4>
  <p>
    Renders up to 150,000 simultaneous entities on a GPU-accelerated 3D globe at 60fps. Smooth, cinematic navigation from orbital view down to street level. Every entity is interactive &mdash; click on a vessel, an aircraft, or a delivery truck to see its full context and history.
  </p>
</div>

<hr />

<h2>Designed for</h2>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Logistics &amp; fleet operations:</strong> Live positions of vehicles during multi-country relocations. Border-crossing alerts, depot arrivals, route deviation warnings.</li>
  <li><strong>Maritime compliance:</strong> Detect anomalies &mdash; vessels going dark in sensitive areas, unusual loitering, ship-to-ship transfers that may indicate sanctions evasion.</li>
  <li><strong>Emergency response:</strong> Unified view of weather, seismic activity, wildfires, and traffic incidents for disaster coordination.</li>
  <li><strong>Supply chain visibility:</strong> Track parcels through distribution networks, correlate delivery patterns with weather impacts.</li>
</ul>

<hr />

<h2>Design principles</h2>

<ol>
  <li><strong>Offline-first:</strong> Once map tiles are cached, the app works without internet. Critical for security-conscious environments and field deployments.</li>
  <li><strong>Zero data exfiltration:</strong> No entity data, queries, or tracking history ever leaves the local machine. All processing happens on your desktop.</li>
  <li><strong>Privacy by default:</strong> Sensitive data &mdash; customer addresses, inventory, asset values &mdash; stays encrypted in a local database.</li>
  <li><strong>Open source foundations:</strong> Built entirely on open-source software. No proprietary dependencies or vendor lock-in.</li>
</ol>

<hr />

<h2>Current status</h2>

<p>
  Tesselage is in active development. The data fusion engine, live feed connectors, and 3D visualization are functional. The AI query layer and fleet management features are under construction.
</p>

